body_html: @ebetica You might need to refactor this class. See the solution 4 in this post. As an alternative, you could export only some functions by annotating them with AT_API instead of the entire class. It could also be that the annotation to the base class is missing.

body: @ebetica You might need to refactor this class. See the solution 4 in this [post](https://www.codeproject.com/Questions/261491/Exporting-classes-from-a-DLL). As an alternative, you could export only some functions by annotating them with AT_API instead of the entire class. It could also be that the annotation to the base class is missing.
